video.title: Nanny 911
video.synopsis: British nannies are sent to the homes of unruly American children in this series, which proves that parents often need as much discipline as the kids.

episodes.synopsis: Nanny Deb answers one family's cry for help. Parents Matt and Karen have lost control of their home to their 4-year-old son and 2-year-old daughter.
episodes.title: The Rock Family

episodes.synopsis: Nanny Yvonne has her work cut out with the Johnston family, consisting of seven girls -- all under the age of 8 -- and two very exhausted parents.
episodes.title: The Johnston Family

episodes.synopsis: Nanny Deb finds Cindy and Tim Paul at their wits' end, with an 8-year-old daughter and a set of 4-year-old triplets ruling the roost.
episodes.title: The Paul Family

episodes.synopsis: Craig, a New York City cop, indulges his kids' every whim to the point of going behind their mom's back; Tracey is exhausted by the kids' behavior.
episodes.title: The McCray Family

episodes.synopsis: With a 7-year-old daughter and boys ages 5, 3 and 2, parents Stevi and John are in over their heads.
episodes.title: The McKelvain Family

episodes.synopsis: With support from Nanny Lillian at Nanny Central and one of her family plans being "brothers for life," can Nanny Deb help the McRoberts family?
episodes.title: The McRoberts Family

episodes.synopsis: Nanny Stella's plan includes congratulating the Lorimor children when they behave and disciplining them when they don't -- but will the strategy work?
episodes.title: The Lorimor Family

episodes.synopsis: Joe and Nina's 10-year-old daughter and set of 8-year-old quadruplets are driving them mad.
episodes.title: The Priore Family

episodes.synopsis: Nanny Deb visits John and Roxanne Sterneman in Southern California, who have three children: Tyler (10), Dana (6) and Lauren (3).
episodes.title: The Sterneman Family

episodes.synopsis: Little did Paul and Deborah know that their dream of wedded bliss would also include three sets of twins.
episodes.title: The Finch Family

episodes.synopsis: After 15 years of marriage, Neil and Amy have fallen out of sync. Meanwhile, their 7-year-old and 3-year-old love junk food and getting into mischief.
episodes.title: The Cubbison Family

episodes.synopsis: Denise Dunleavy has a problem. She has four rambunctious boys, a daughter with Down syndrome and a husband who's never there.
episodes.title: The Dunleavy Family

episodes.synopsis: A couple lives in cramped quarters with their five mischievous children, three dogs, three cats, two rabbits and a hamster.
episodes.title: The King Family

episodes.synopsis: Shortly after the birth of their first child, Sal, David and Dawn decided it would be nice to have one more baby -- and ended up with quadruplets.
episodes.title: The Amico Family

episodes.synopsis: When it's time for bed, young James and Jacob are so scared and resistant that you'd think they were being punished and thrown to the lions.
episodes.title: The Lawrence Family

episodes.synopsis: A recently widowed young mother of two has found that she needs to fill the role of both father and mother after the untimely death of her husband.
episodes.title: The Dickson Family

episodes.synopsis: Married for seven years and on call 24 hours a day, seven days a week, Ann and Jim are the adoptive parents of 32 kids.
episodes.title: Silcock Family Special
